dsiter.row

Class RowShape

  • java.lang.Object
    • dsiter.row.RowShape

  • public class RowShape
extends java.lang.Object
    Class that describes the "shape" of a Row. The shape of a Row is simply the size of each array in the row (i.e. the number of ints, the number of longs, the number of floats, etc).

      • RowShape

        public RowShape(ColumnDescriptor[] cds)
        Construct a new RowShape from a set of ColumnDescriptors (counts the number of columns of each type)

        Note: this will fail to construct an accurate RowShape if the Rows in question contain "deleted" values that are not described by any of the passed ColumnDescriptors.

        Parameters:
        cds - The columns that describe the Row in question

        public int getNum(ColumnType type)
        Get the number of values of the specified type in this shape.

        For example, if type == ColumnType.INT, this is equivalent to calling getNumInts()

      • incrNum

        public void incrNum(ColumnType type)
        Increment the number of values of the specified type in this shape.

        This is equivalent to (but more efficient than) calling setNum(type, getNum(type)+1)

        Parameters:
        type - The type whose count is to be incremented

      • add

        public static RowShape add(RowShape shape1,
                           RowShape shape2)
        Return a new RowShape instance whose counts are the sums of the counts of the passed RowShapes. Will not modify either shape1 or shape2.
        Parameters:
        shape1 - One shape to be summed
        shape2 - The other shape to be summed
        Returns:
        A new RowShape instance representing the sum of the two parameters

      • add

        public RowShape add(RowShape other)
        Return a new RowShape instance whose counts are the sums of the current RowShape and the passed RowShape. Will not modify either the current RowShape or the passed RowShape.

        shapeA.add(shapeB) is equivalent to RowShape.add(shapeA, shapeB)

        Parameters:
        other - The RowShape to be summed with the current RowShape
        Returns:
        A new RowShape instance representing the sum of the two RowShapes
